The definition of `image g` is `λ v => g v`.
The definition of `image f` is `λ u => f u`.

So `image g (image f u)` becomes `g (f u)`.
And we have `h1 : g (f u) = u`.

So the goal becomes `g (f u) = u`, which is exactly `h1`.

Therefore, `exact h1` would complete the proof, or `simp_all` is able to use `h1` to close the goal.

