- `image f` is the set `{ f u | u ∈ U }` which is a subset of `V`
- `image g` is the set `{ g v | v ∈ V }` which is a subset of `U`
- `image g ∘ image f` is the function that takes an element `v` in `V` (if it's in `image f`), maps it to `g v` in `U` (if it's in `image g`), and then maps that back to `f (g v)` in `V`

